headline: Phillips 66 trims portfolio with German and Austria retail sale amid Elliott pressure
summary: Elliott, which holds a $2.5 billion stake in Phillips 66, has been pushing for major changes at the company, including the potential spin-off or sale of its midstream business, and is seeking to refresh the board to align with its strategic goals.  Elliott did not immediately respond to a request on the divestment announcement.
